Practical no 5
AIM: Create an html page with fields, eno, name, age, desg, salary. Now on submit this
data to a JSP page which will update the employee table of database with matching eno.
CREATE TABLE employee (
                  eno INT PRIMARY KEY,
                  name VARCHAR(100),
                  age INT,
                  designation VARCHAR(50),
                  salary DECIMAL(10, 2)
                  );
INSERT INTO employee (eno, name, age, designation, salary) VALUES
                            (101, ‘VINAY CHIVILKAR, 23, 'Software Engineer', 22000.00),
                            (102, ‘Ankit Rawat’, 28, 'Project Manager', 75000.00),
                            (103, SHIVAM CHIVILKAR, 35, 'Team Lead', 65000.00);
5B: Create a JSP page to demonstrate the use of Expression language.
5C: Create a JSP application to demonstrate the use of JSTL.

PRACTICAL 6
6A: Create a Currency Converter application using EJB.
6B: Develop a Simple Room Reservation System Application Using EJB.
CREATE TABLE book (
                       roomId INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
                       RoomType VARCHAR(50),
                       cust VARCHAR(100) DEFAULT '',
                       mob VARCHAR(15) DEFAULT '',
                       status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'Not Booked',
                       charges DECIMAL(10, 2)
                       );
INSERT INTO book (RoomType, status, charges) VALUES ('Single', 'Not Booked', 1500.00),
                        ('Double', 'Not Booked', 2500.00),
                        ('Delux', 'Not Booked', 3500.00),
                        ('Super', 'Not Booked', 4500.00),
                        ('Single', 'Not Booked', 1500.00),
                        ('Double', 'Not Booked', 2500.00),
                        ('Delux', 'Not Booked', 3500.00),
                        ('Super', 'Not Booked', 4500.00);

